10:
If you haven't brought candy...
prepare to be dissected!
12:
Uh, it's not candy, but how does
some dinner sound?
16:
A home-cooked meal prepared by
Alk, eh? That... is more than
acceptable!
21:
I'd better get some candy for the
rest of the gang just in case.
25:
Talk about a letdown. You used to
be so adorable when I scared you!
29:
Yeah... before he realized you would
do this EVERY time.
37:
But yeah, some grub would hit the
spot right now—I've just reached a
breakthrough in my experiment!
41:
Another one, huh? Well, I'll just leave
a plate and be on my way then—
52:
Did you press what I think you just
pressed?
55:
There goes the ghost I was
experimenting on...
60:
Why'd you put such an important
switch in a place like that?!
66:
Well, I knew where the button was,
so it was fine—or so I thought.
70:
Anyway, looks like it scurried off
somewhere outside.
76:
Good thing no one here's afraid of
ghosts, right?
80:
Yes... quite the contrary, actually. 
I'd be more concerned for the ghost 
at this point.
84: Hehe... That's Starview for you, right?
89:
Still, we've got a situation on our
hands!
93:
Not to worry! I present to you... 
The Boogie Catcher!
99:
Don't worry about it—ready to bust a
ghost?
108:
Yikes. I suppose I'll be the one to
clean this up.
111:
H-hey, those are ingredients for
tonight's dinner!
121:
I'll draw its attention to the kitchen,
so just get ready to catch it. Ready?
127:
Born ready! Nobody messes with MY
ingredients.
152:
Uh... Sorry. I don't think this one's
gonna be of much use anymore.
156:
You failed to mention their 
ectoplasm would be so... slimy.
159:
No worries. 'Preciate the help, you
two!
161:
And Light, would you mind sharing 
some of that slimy stuff with me later? 
And while you're at it, let me dissect 
you—for science, of course!
169:
Why are you experimenting on
ghosts anyway?
173:
I've recently taken an interest in the
relationship between energy and
life-forms.
175:
And wouldn't you know it, ghosts are
an anomaly in both fields!
178:
Not only that, but catching a
low-level ghost in Palpebra is a
cinch—especially on Halloween!
185:
Oh, yeah. Ghosts totally love a good
shindig!
187:
Here's an idea. Since you're the one
who lost my specimen, you'll help
me catch a new one. Deal?
196:
Heh. Don't you worry, I'll make sure
it's worth your while!
200: Worth my while? Don't tell me...
204:
You guessed it! Seasquirt candy! 
Just in time for Halloween.
207:
Of course it is. Why would I ever think
it could've been something else?
211:
Enough chatter, Alk! There's science
to be captured!
